## Bevy version

Bevy "0.16" via cargo

## \[Optional\] Relevant system information

cargo 1.86

SystemInfo { os: "Windows 11 Home", kernel: "26100", cpu: "AMD Ryzen 9 7950X 16-Core Processor", core_count: "16", memory: "63.2 GiB" }    
AdapterInfo { name: "NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4070 SUPER", vendor: 4318, device: 10115, device_type: DiscreteGpu, driver: "NVIDIA", driver_info: "572.70", backend: Vulkan }
GPU preprocessing is fully supported on this device.

## What you did

Point Light shadows completely wrong after looking away.  Only initially occurs when camera is outside of the lights `range` and pointed away, but is not fixed by re-entering the `range`.

## What went wrong

expected: shadows like normal, same as 0.15.3 or if I don't get too far and/or don't look away from the light
what happened: shadows are wrong - see video

## Additional information

changing bevy to "0.15.3" results in not seeing the issue.

Initial Problem:

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e3470439-45ce-4197-ad16-ee4d73cfd785


I made a minimal repro (less visually crazy, but the cubes shadows will disappear and reappear when looking away and back (only if far enough away, a bit past the edge of the disk or so)

Cargo.toml
```
[package]
name = "glitch"
version = "0.1.0"
edition = "2024"

[dependencies]
bevy = "0.16"
```

src/main.rs
```
use bevy::prelude::*;

fn main() {
    App::new()
        .add_plugins(DefaultPlugins)
        .insert_resource(ClearColor(Color::BLACK))
        .add_systems(Startup, startup)
        .add_systems(Update, update)
        .run();
}

fn startup(
    mut commands: Commands,
    mut meshes: ResMut<Assets<Mesh>>,
    mut materials: ResMut<Assets<StandardMaterial>>,
) {
    commands.spawn((Camera3d::default(), Transform::from_xyz(0.0, 5.0, 8.0)));
    commands.spawn((
        Transform::from_xyz(0.0, 0.0, 0.0),
        Mesh3d(meshes.add(Cylinder::new(20.0, 0.5))),
        MeshMaterial3d(materials.add(Color::WHITE)),
    ));
    for i in 0..10 {
        commands.spawn((
            Mesh3d(meshes.add(Cuboid::from_length(1.0))),
            MeshMaterial3d(materials.add(Color::srgb(0.2, 0.3, 0.8))),
            Transform::from_xyz(0.0, 2.5 + (i as f32 * 2.0), -2.0 - (i as f32 * 0.5)),
        ));
    }
    commands.spawn((
        PointLight {
            shadows_enabled: true,
            ..Default::default()
        },
        Transform::from_xyz(0.0, 8.0, 0.0),
    ));
}

fn update(
    time: Res<Time>,
    camera: Single<&mut Transform, With<Camera3d>>,
    keyboard_input: Res<ButtonInput<KeyCode>>,
) {
    let delta_time = time.delta_secs();
    let mut camera_transform = camera.into_inner();

    if keyboard_input.pressed(KeyCode::KeyQ) {
        camera_transform.rotate_y(3.0 * delta_time);
    }
    if keyboard_input.pressed(KeyCode::KeyE) {
        camera_transform.rotate_y(-3.0 * delta_time);
    }

    let mut dir = Vec3::ZERO;
    if keyboard_input.pressed(KeyCode::KeyW) {
        dir.z -= 1.0;
    }
    if keyboard_input.pressed(KeyCode::KeyS) {
        dir.z += 1.0;
    }
    if keyboard_input.pressed(KeyCode::KeyA) {
        dir.x -= 1.0;
    }
    if keyboard_input.pressed(KeyCode::KeyD) {
        dir.x += 1.0;
    }

    let dir = camera_transform.rotation * dir;
    camera_transform.translation += dir * 12.0 * delta_time;
}
```

